reviewText:
RTS: Subjective score: 8/10


So you think you have the brains for strategy ?

Well, this baby is all about strategy (it comes down to tactics as well as it is real time strategy, but if we compare this to - lets say - WC III, then WC III was heavily tactical RTS). In this game, you might send your troops in blind suicide mission to harass the enemy only to get some precious seconds to manage your economy/constructions.

A good commander will have to:
- Control key strategic points;
- Pick the right types of constructs for the right type of the enemy's defenses/incoming attack waves;
- Know when to strike & when to dig in and focus on technology;
- Manage Land, Air, Naval (+submersible) units;
- Utilise Intel (scout, radar, optical vision, radar stealth, even optical stealth);
- Utilise strategic weapons such as artillery support for those turtle types.
